  "text": "## Consumer Offset Management Architecture in Apache Kafka\n\nApache Kafka implements a sophisticated consumer offset management system that enables consumer groups to persist and retrieve committed offsets for topic partitions. The architecture spans multiple layers from protocol definitions to broker-side coordination.\n\n### Core Offset Storage\n\nThe `__consumer_offsets` internal topic is the central repository for all consumer group offset information. The OffsetAndMetadata class (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/OffsetAndMetadata.java) serves as the server-side representation of committed offsets, storing the offset value, optional leader epoch, and custom metadata. This is complemented by the client-side OffsetAndMetadata class (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/OffsetAndMetadata.java) that consumers use to commit offsets.\n\n### GroupCoordinator Architecture\n\nThe GroupCoordinator interface (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinator.java) defines the contract for offset management operations. It's implemented by GroupCoordinatorService (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinatorService.java), which delegates to GroupCoordinatorShard instances for distributed coordination. The GroupCoordinatorShard (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinatorShard.java) manages in-memory state for specific topic partitions.\n\n### Offset Management Operations\n\n**Offset Commit Handler**: The OffsetMetadataManager (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/OffsetMetadataManager.java) is responsible for handling offset commits. It validates commit requests, updates offset state, and persists offset records to the __consumer_offsets topic. The GroupCoordinatorRecordHelpers (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinatorRecordHelpers.java) provides utilities for creating and converting offset commit records, including legacy format support.\n\n**Offset Fetch Handler**: When clients request to fetch committed offsets, the OffsetMetadataManager's fetchOffsets method retrieves the stored offsets from its in-memory state. The fetchOffsets operation in GroupCoordinatorShard coordinates the retrieval and formats responses according to the protocol version.\n\n**Offset Deletion**: The deleteOffsets method in OffsetMetadataManager handles offset deletion requests, creating tombstone records for offset keys to remove them during log compaction.\n\n### Request/Response Protocol\n\nThe OffsetCommitRequest (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/requests/OffsetCommitRequest.java) and OffsetCommitResponse (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/requests/OffsetCommitResponse.java) classes handle the protocol for committing offsets. Similarly, OffsetFetchRequest (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/requests/OffsetFetchRequest.java) and OffsetFetchResponse (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/requests/OffsetFetchResponse.java) handle offset retrieval, and OffsetDeleteRequest (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/requests/OffsetDeleteRequest.java) supports offset deletion via the admin API.\n\n### Broker-Side Request Handling\n\nThe KafkaApis.scala file (core/src/main/scala/kafka/server/KafkaApis.scala) contains the broker-level handlers: handleOffsetCommitRequest, handleOffsetFetchRequest, and handleOffsetDeleteRequest. These handlers parse protocol requests, perform authorization checks, and delegate to the GroupCoordinator for actual offset operations.\n\n### Client-Side Offset Management\n\nThe ConsumerCoordinator (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/ConsumerCoordinator.java) manages offset commit operations on the consumer side. The CommitRequestManager (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/CommitRequestManager.java) handles queueing and retrying of offset commit requests. The OffsetCommitCallbackInvoker (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/OffsetCommitCallbackInvoker.java) invokes user callbacks upon successful offset commits.\n\n### Group Types and Offset Management\n\nBoth ClassicGroup (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/classic/ClassicGroup.java) and ConsumerGroup (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/modern/consumer/ConsumerGroup.java) implement the Group interface and support offset management operations. The GroupMetadataManager (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupMetadataManager.java) manages group membership state and coordinates with the OffsetMetadataManager for offset operations.\n\n### Offset Expiry and Compaction\n\nOffsets are automatically expired based on retention policy configured in GroupCoordinatorConfig (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinatorConfig.java). The LogCleanerManager (storage/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/storage/internals/log/LogCleanerManager.java) handles log compaction of the __consumer_offsets topic, removing expired offset records via tombstones.\n\n### Metrics and Monitoring\n\nThe GroupCoordinatorMetrics (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/metrics/GroupCoordinatorMetrics.java) and GroupCoordinatorMetricsShard (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/metrics/GroupCoordinatorMetricsShard.java) track offset commit operations. The OffsetCommitMetricsManager (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/metrics/OffsetCommitMetricsManager.java) provides client-side metrics for offset commit performance.\n\n### Admin Operations\n\nThe DeleteConsumerGroupOffsetsHandler (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/admin/internals/DeleteConsumerGroupOffsetsHandler.java) and ListConsumerGroupOffsetsResult (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/admin/ListConsumerGroupOffsetsResult.java) support administrative operations for deleting and listing consumer group offsets.\n"
}

